==English==
===Etymology===
From ''[[marathon]]'', the events described by words made from this suffix being of a great length, as a marathon is a race of a great length

===Suffix===
'''-athon''' (''sometimes'' '''-thon''' ''after a vowel'')

#Used to form words meaning a greatly extended period of any activity, usually for the purpose of [[fundraising]].
#:''walkathon''
#:''telethon''
